08:47.461 --> 08:49.729
No. Why would you say that?

08:49.763 --> 08:51.831
I don't know.
We seem to have our differences.

08:51.866 --> 08:53.633
- It's a gift.
- For what?

08:53.667 --> 08:55.868
Look, I don't know
what you did to the guy,

08:55.903 --> 08:58.604
but it's really really important
to him that you like him.

08:58.639 --> 09:00.172
It's amazing to me that you don't.

09:00.207 --> 09:02.976
Oh no, I like him fine, Johnny.
I just don't date celebrities.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.312
Yeah?
Well, who do you date?

09:05.346 --> 09:09.250
Well, my last boyfriend was head of
pediatric surgery at Johns Hopkins.

09:09.284 --> 09:12.760
A surgeon? Eh, he probably didn't
have the time to treat you right.

09:12.926 --> 09:16.291
Look, I know that
a woman of your stature

09:16.326 --> 09:19.495
may have preconceived notions about a
guy like Vince, but you should know,

09:19.529 --> 09:22.198
especially after interviewing
him, he's not just some actor.

09:22.232 --> 09:25.067
He's smart...
Maybe not John...

09:25.102 --> 09:26.535
- What's his name?
- Hopkins.

09:26.570 --> 09:28.985
Hopkins kind of smart,
but he's smart.

09:29.151 --> 09:33.541
More importantly, he's a
friend and a brother...

09:33.575 --> 09:35.643
The best I know of both.

09:37.279 --> 09:39.179
It's very sweet of you
to look out for him.

09:39.214 --> 09:42.716
Well, that's all he does
for me, so I owe him.

09:42.750 --> 09:45.653
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

09:51.126 --> 09:53.694
<i>Knock knock.</i>

09:53.729 --> 09:56.054
Oh no.
Are you crying, Ari?

09:56.220 --> 10:00.135
- No, I'm not crying.
- You need a good dose of Dr. Marcus.

10:00.170 --> 10:01.604
Do you like this script?

10:01.638 --> 10:04.229
I loved it.

10:04.395 --> 10:05.897
