- You don't have 3 kids in private school

13:02.454 --> 13:04.826
- in Greenwich, Connecticut, do you, Turtle?
- No.

13:04.992 --> 13:06.924
Well, you don't know how
expensive it is then, do you?

13:06.958 --> 13:09.292
- No.
- <i>Turtle, find another way.</i>

13:09.327 --> 13:11.561
<i>And don't try to guilt me.
It doesn't work.</i>

13:11.596 --> 13:13.751
Okay.

13:13.917 --> 13:16.031
I mean, am I talking
about this too much?

13:16.066 --> 13:17.633
No, I like Sloan bashing.

13:17.667 --> 13:20.702
I just feel like everything she's
ever said to me has been a lie.

13:20.737 --> 13:23.605
- "I don't date actors"?
- That's the biggest bullshit line of all time.

13:23.673 --> 13:25.041
I used to say I don't fuck agents.

13:25.075 --> 13:26.976
Then I married one and he fucked me.

13:27.010 --> 13:29.346
- I'm so pissed.
- Let it all out, E.

13:29.380 --> 13:31.349
You're the only one
I can talk to about this too.

13:31.383 --> 13:33.384
Trust me, my friends
are over hearing about it.

13:33.418 --> 13:36.054
Hate for the McQuewicks
is something I will never tire of.

13:36.088 --> 13:38.757
Plus, your anger
really got you going.

13:38.791 --> 13:41.193
Really?
What do you mean?

13:41.228 --> 13:44.430
I mean this is the first
really good sex we've had.

13:44.464 --> 13:46.732
- Really?
- I mean for me.

13:46.766 --> 13:49.402
- I'm sure it's always been great for you.
- Yeah.

13:49.436 --> 13:51.270
Let's be honest.
You don't really hate her.

13:51.305 --> 13:52.906
Are you kidding me?

13:52.940 --> 13:55.875
- No. I think you love her.
- Not even a little bit.

13:57.411 --> 14:00.413
- Hello?
- Your ex-fiancee

14:00.447 --> 14:02.800
sipping drinks with a certain
frizzy-headed actor.

14:02.966 --> 14:05.803
- What?
- Sloan and Galecki are at the Farmers Market, E.

14:05.969 --> 14:07.638
You've gotta be fucking kidding me.

14:07.804 --> 14:09.588
You want me to go crack him
in the head or something?

14:11.258 --> 14:14.394
No, leave it alone.
I'm over it.

14:14.428 --> 14:17.497
- <i>Okay.</i>
- Okay, thanks.

14:17.531 --> 14:19.599
Later.

14:19.633 --> 14:22.268
What happened?

14:22.303 --> 14:24.804
Sloan and Galecki are
at the Farmers Market.

14:24.838 --> 14:27.373
Ah, but you're over it.

14:30.277 --> 14:32.445
I'll fucking kill somebody.

14:32.480 --> 14:35.081
Do you want to fuck
one more time before you do?

14:36.917 --> 14:39.151
- Sophia Lear?
- You know her?

14:39.186 --> 14:40.653
Of course I do.
Great writer.

14:40.687 --> 14:42.655
Did a piece on me a few years ago.

14:42.689 --> 14:44.992
- I didn't know that.
- Yeah. She's smart.

14:45.026 --> 14:47.694
- That I know.
- And sexy.

14:47.728 --> 14:49.663
Yeah, but that's not it.

14:49.697 --> 14:51.197
I've never had this feeling before.

14:51.232 --> 14:53.934
- Maybe it's the rejection.
- No, I don't think so.

14:53.968 --> 14:56.170
Wow, I've never
seen you so infatuated

14:56.205 --> 14:57.739
by a girl before, except maybe Sasha.

14:57.773 --> 14:59.607
And you were all drugged out.

14:59.642 --> 15:01.576
I'm serious about this, Ari.

15:01.611 --> 15:03.579
You ever have that feeling
where you just know?

15:03.613 --> 15:05.314
- Immediately?
- Yeah, mm-hmm.

15:05.348 --> 15:07.116
Once, 20 years ago
when I met my wife.

15:07.150 --> 15:10.452
- Aw, I'm sorry, Ari.
- Hey, listen. It lasted 20 years.

15:10.486 --> 15:14.022
And if you really do feel this way,
then fight for it.

15:14.056 --> 15:16.158
- Thanks, Ari.
- Ari, he's in a meeting.

15:16.192 --> 15:17.960
Listen, if he would have
called me back,

15:17.994 --> 15:19.995
we could've avoided
me interrupting it.

15:20.030 --> 15:21.863
I'm just with him.

15:25.101 --> 15:27.402
Busy day, Phil?

15:27.437 --> 15:30.471
Jesus Christ.
Ari, what the fuck?

15:30.637 --> 15:32.807
<i>It's okay, Robin.
Uh, ahem.</i>

15:32.974 --> 15:35.976
Come on in.

15:37.078 --> 15:38.878
<i>I was going to call you back.</i>

15:38.913 --> 15:40.546
No, you weren't, which is nuts.

15:40.581 --> 15:42.748
Look, I love the script, Vince.

15:42.783 --> 15:46.418
- But you're mad at my brother.
- No no, it's... it's not that.

15:46.453 --> 15:48.388
Business is business,
strikes are strikes.

15:48.422 --> 15:51.524
- When it's over, there's no grudges held.
- So what's the problem then?

15:51.558 --> 15:53.327
Moonves wants a bigger name.

15:53.493 --> 15:56.061
- Oh, come on.
- Chris Noth, Christian Slater,

15:56.095 --> 15:58.463
- one of the good-looking guys that was on "Lost."
- Oh my God.

15:58.497 --> 16:01.099
It's a fucking TV movie, Phil.

16:01.133 --> 16:04.297
- I know, but...
- No buts, Phil. You're pissed.

16:04.463 --> 16:06.372
Is that it?
You're holding a grudge, Phil?

16:06.406 --> 16:09.742
Are those the cookies my brother
sent you, all smashed up?

16:09.777 --> 16:12.713
Okay, fine, I...

16:12.747 --> 16:16.050
I am pissed and I am hurt

16:16.084 --> 16:20.722
because I am the only person
in this fucking town

16:20.756 --> 16:23.224
that has stood by your brother.

16:23.259 --> 16:26.494
And instead of working with
me, he just fucking walked.

16:26.529 --> 16:28.997
<i>And I still have to work with him</i>

16:29.031 --> 16:31.165
on "Johnny Bananas"
every day... every day.

16:31.199 --> 16:33.734
So why the fuck would I want
to work with him

16:33.768 --> 16:35.469
on something else too every day, huh?

16:35.503 --> 16:38.905
- Um, I am pissed.
- You have to look at the bigger picture.

16:38.940 --> 16:40.440
Johnny's going to kill this.

16:40.474 --> 16:42.709
Walsh wrote an incredible
script with his voice in mind

16:42.743 --> 16:44.377
and he's gonna direct
the hell out of it.

16:44.411 --> 16:46.513
I have no doubts
about the movie, Vince.

16:46.547 --> 16:48.882
- I don't.
- How do we get you over this, Phil?

16:49.951 --> 16:51.485
I don't know if I can.

16:51.519 --> 16:53.320
How about your charity?
What are you working on now?

16:53.354 --> 16:55.489
Still the German Shepherd thing?

16:55.523 --> 16:57.758
Yeah, it's horrible what people
do to that beautiful breed.

16:57.792 --> 17:01.896
- $5,000 from me just to say yes to this.
- $5,000, Ari?

17:01.930 --> 17:05.191
Wow. That might feed
10 dogs for a week.

17:05.357 --> 17:07.702
I'm going through a fuckin'
divorce right now, Phil!

17:07.736 --> 17:10.906
- I'll give you $100,000.
- Really?

17:10.940 --> 17:13.075
But we don't mention this again.

17:20.184 --> 17:22.124
- What happened?
- We're making a movie.

17:22.290 --> 17:25.154
- Seriously?
- Prime time, c.B.S.

17:25.188 --> 17:27.122
Yes!
Come over here.

17:27.156 --> 17:30.692
Oh, I can't thank you
enough, baby bro.

17:30.726 --> 17:32.294
- You too, Ari.
- Ah.

17:32.328 --> 17:33.795
All right.

17:33.829 --> 17:35.029
Ah!

17:36.596 --> 17:39.533
- Come on, Amaré.
- <i>Come on, Amaré what?</i>

17:39.568 --> 17:42.186
- You think cash grow on trees?
- Your trees maybe.

17:42.352 --> 17:45.106
I gotta think if I want to put the
original 250 in with you, Turtle.

17:45.272 --> 17:47.741
I'll telling you, Amaré, you
don't want to miss out on this.

17:47.775 --> 17:50.027
I got everybody.
I got Melo. I got Eli.

17:50.193 --> 17:52.678
- <i>I got Strahan--</i>
- Oh, you got Strahan, huh?

17:52.712 --> 17:55.180
- Who got me for what?
- I spoke to him today.

17:55.215 --> 17:56.993
- Hey, Turtle's on this Don Peppe thing.
- Oh yeah.

17:57.159 --> 17:59.584
- <i>Did he call you for more money?</i>
- <i>Oh yeah.</i>

17:59.618 --> 18:01.998
- What did you tell him?
- I told him to go fuck himself.

18:02.164 --> 18:04.657
- Amaré, listen...
- Hey, go fuck yourself, Turtle.

18:06.326 --> 18:08.895
All right.

18:12.366 --> 18:15.301
- Hey, Alex.
- Turtle, why are you guilting Tex?

18:15.468 --> 18:17.971
- Listen, I wasn't...
- <i>And why can't you put any more money</i>

18:18.005 --> 18:19.539
<i>into this sure thing
anyway?</i>

18:19.574 --> 18:21.075
Because I don't have any more money.

18:21.109 --> 18:22.343
What are you talking about?

18:22.377 --> 18:23.644
I thought you were in
that avion tequila deal.

18:23.810 --> 18:26.012
- Yeah, I made a few bucks.
- <i>A few bucks?</i>

18:26.047 --> 18:27.547
I heard it went public today.

18:28.683 --> 18:31.717
- What?
- <i>Call Tex and apologize.</i>

18:31.752 --> 18:34.086
We're trying to win a ring around here.

18:38.725 --> 18:40.870
Hey, anyone using this chair?

18:41.036 --> 18:43.748
- You must be kidding.
- What? Is it weird seeing me here?

18:43.914 --> 18:45.664
I mean we used to
eat here all the time.

18:45.698 --> 18:47.733
- I picked this place, Eric.
- <i>Really?</i>

18:47.767 --> 18:49.401
- Did you, Johnny?
- Hi, Sloan.

18:49.436 --> 18:51.737
Are you fucking serious?

18:51.771 --> 18:53.339
Eric, what are you doing here?

18:53.373 --> 18:55.841
- He's here to upset me.
- We're here to have lunch.

18:55.875 --> 18:58.110
- Oh, then we'll leave.
- Oh, what a shame.

18:58.144 --> 19:00.078
Melinda, what are you, like 60?

19:00.113 --> 19:01.713
Isn't this a little beneath you?

19:01.747 --> 19:03.809
No, this sort of Drama
keeps me feeling young.

19:03.975 --> 19:06.084
- That and all the plastic surgery.
- Not even a syringe.

19:06.119 --> 19:07.897
Why don't you mind your
own business, Galecki?

19:08.063 --> 19:11.400
- You interrupted our lunch.
- <i>Yeah well, it's a free country.</i>

19:11.566 --> 19:14.028
So if you wouldn't mind telling your
boyfriend here to leave Melinda alone...

19:14.194 --> 19:16.989
Your cougar may tell you what to do,

19:17.155 --> 19:19.597
- but I don't boss my men around.
- Yeah? That's funny.

19:19.631 --> 19:21.999
You certainly had a lot of suggestions
for me when we were dating.

19:22.034 --> 19:24.413
Eric, would you like to take
this around the corner?

19:24.579 --> 19:26.290
I'll bang your smug
face out right here.

19:26.456 --> 19:29.460
- Respected actors don't get in public brawls.
- Ha!

19:29.626 --> 19:31.477
Oh really? Is that why you're
dating an actor, Sloan?

19:31.511 --> 19:34.547
- Because he's "respected"?
- This is so fucking stupid.

19:34.581 --> 19:36.782
Stupid?
Stupid how?

19:36.817 --> 19:40.486
- You mean like Seth Green was stupid?
- Oh my God, you're joking.

19:40.521 --> 19:43.089
- What about Seth Green?
- Sloan hit that too.

19:43.123 --> 19:44.657
- Really?
- No.

19:44.692 --> 19:46.793
- Believe what you want.
- Look, you started it.

19:46.827 --> 19:48.861
I called you after the
last time we hooked up.

19:48.896 --> 19:51.264
You basically said you used
me and you were moving on.

19:51.298 --> 19:54.200
- I'm trying.
- By fucking my clients at the Farmers Market?

19:54.234 --> 19:55.735
- All right.
- You're running around

19:55.769 --> 19:58.438
with my ex-stepmother
who's twice your age.

19:58.472 --> 20:01.274
I needed some youth after
your corpse of a father.

20:01.308 --> 20:04.176
I never figured you for
the revenge type, Eric.

20:04.210 --> 20:06.778
And I never figured you for a slut.

20:10.950 --> 20:14.219
Oh, you're fired.
Go fuck yourself.

20:16.622 --> 20:18.723
Well, so what did the bank say?

20:18.757 --> 20:20.191
Well, the loan isn't a problem.

20:20.225 --> 20:22.560
I just have to
personally guarantee it.

20:22.627 --> 20:25.329
- How does that make you feel?
- Not good.

20:25.364 --> 20:27.598
But business is good.

20:27.633 --> 20:29.434
Yeah, business is good.
It's not great.

20:29.468 --> 20:32.404
It's just not where I wanted to be

20:32.438 --> 20:34.373
at this stage in life, you know.

20:34.407 --> 20:36.542
Sometimes I wonder if I have worked

20:36.576 --> 20:38.678
all this time to end up with nothing.

20:43.451 --> 20:46.620
- It's your wife.
- Well, it could be my kids.

20:46.654 --> 20:51.457
- I didn't say anything.
- I'm just not going to get it.

20:51.492 --> 20:53.593
<i>Don't ignore your kids because of me.</i>

20:53.628 --> 20:56.229
- It could be my wife.
- Look, it could be your kids.

20:56.263 --> 20:58.465
<i>Well, I'm... you know,
I'm going to call them back.</i>

20:58.499 --> 21:00.926
- Jesus.
- What do you want me to do?

21:01.092 --> 21:03.369
- Am I wasting my time here, Ari?
- Dana--

21:03.404 --> 21:05.505
because I don't have time to waste.

21:05.539 --> 21:07.607
You did this when we were 20.

21:07.641 --> 21:09.341
<i>I was emotional.</i>

21:09.375 --> 21:12.511
I'm 40 now and I'm logical.

21:14.413 --> 21:16.280
I don't know where this is going.

21:16.315 --> 21:19.884
I know that I get a great
feeling when I'm with you.

21:19.918 --> 21:21.719
But?

21:25.190 --> 21:28.092
But I still love my wife.

21:30.362 --> 21:32.196
Then go back to her.

21:32.230 --> 21:34.799
- She doesn't want me.
- I don't believe that.

21:34.834 --> 21:37.169
She just wants something
you're not giving her.

21:37.203 --> 21:39.905
- What?
- I don't know.

21:39.940 --> 21:43.242
You're smart.
Figure it out.

21:46.614 --> 21:48.048
Don't be mad at me.

21:48.082 --> 21:51.451
I am sad, Ari.

21:51.486 --> 21:55.590
But you're honest,
so how can I be mad?

22:04.901 --> 22:08.569
<i>We caught up with billionaire
mavericks owner mark Cuban</i>

22:08.604 --> 22:10.972
<i>who just made
another boatload of money</i>

22:11.006 --> 22:12.831
<i>on his tequila company going public.</i>

22:12.997 --> 22:16.543
<i>Hmm, wonder how a super-rich guy
celebrates</i> <i>something like that.</i>

22:19.213 --> 22:21.280
<i>Oh, just like
the rest of us.</i>

22:22.816 --> 22:24.134
Hello?

22:24.300 --> 22:26.136
Oh, hi.
This is Sophia Lear for Vince.

22:26.302 --> 22:28.889
<i>I think the cellphone number
he gave me was wrong.</i>

22:28.924 --> 22:30.992
- Oh hey. It's Turtle.
- <i>Hello, Turtle.</i>

22:31.026 --> 22:32.960
- Did you get the movie?
- Yes, I did.

22:32.995 --> 22:35.797
- <i>Did you like it?</i>
- I honestly didn't know what to make of it.

22:35.831 --> 22:37.298
He is very persistent,
your friend, though,

22:37.333 --> 22:39.191
- isn't he?
- <i>Not usually.</i>

22:39.357 --> 22:42.069
To be honest, I've actually never seen
him put any real effort in with a girl.

22:42.235 --> 22:43.872
<i>You made a real impression on him.</i>

22:43.906 --> 22:45.707
This is just so bizarre.

22:45.741 --> 22:47.142
You don't even know bizarre.

22:47.176 --> 22:49.043
This morning the guy was reading
"the Wall Street Journal"

22:49.078 --> 22:50.678
'cause he doesn't think
he's smart enough for you.

22:50.713 --> 22:52.713
Maybe he's not.

22:52.747 --> 22:56.383
<i>Sophia, I'm just going to say
a couple of things to you.</i>

22:56.417 --> 22:59.503
First, Vince is the best guy
I've ever known.

22:59.669 --> 23:01.654
He takes care of so many people

23:01.689 --> 23:03.690
and makes so much happen for them

23:03.724 --> 23:05.926
and doesn't expect
anything in return.

23:06.092 --> 23:07.894
<i>You know this guy paid off
my mother's mortgage</i>

23:07.929 --> 23:10.731
<i>when they were going to repossess
her house and he never told us?</i>

23:10.765 --> 23:13.033
And this was years ago
when he only had a few bucks.

23:13.068 --> 23:15.185
That's very sweet.

23:15.351 --> 23:18.907
Just give him a shot, Sophia.
I swear it'll be worth it.

23:18.941 --> 23:21.309
Most bizarre courtship of my life.

23:21.343 --> 23:22.944
That's how we roll.

23:22.978 --> 23:24.479
Tell him I leave town tomorrow,

23:24.513 --> 23:26.047
and if he can meet me for a drink

23:26.081 --> 23:27.948
at the chateau at 9:00, then--

23:27.983 --> 23:29.491
<i>I guarantee you he will be there.</i>

23:29.657 --> 23:31.718
<i>Nice talking to you, Turtle.</i>

23:31.752 --> 23:33.887
You too, Sophia. Bye.

23:36.123 --> 23:38.057
You want to shoot in Prague?

23:38.092 --> 23:39.792
I don't care if we shoot
in Culver City.

23:39.827 --> 23:42.337
I'm so happy.
Yo, Turtle!

23:42.503 --> 23:44.531
- Yo.
- <i>Vince got me the movie.</i>

23:44.565 --> 23:46.700
Really?
That's amazing.

23:46.734 --> 23:50.070
- And Billy's directing.
- Redemption for all.

23:50.104 --> 23:53.515
- Wow, that's incredible.
- Isn't it?

23:53.681 --> 23:57.436
- I got some news for you too, Vin.
- Do tell.

23:57.602 --> 24:00.348
- You want the good or the bad first?
- You know I always go good.

24:00.382 --> 24:03.192
- Sophia called right before you walked in.
- She did? What did she say?

24:03.358 --> 24:05.187
- She wants to meet for a drink tonight.
- Really?

24:05.221 --> 24:07.696
- Ah.
- <i>I think she thought the movie was weird,</i>

24:07.862 --> 24:09.907
but I told her a few stories of
my own that may have turned her.

24:10.073 --> 24:13.561
- I really appreciate that.
- Yeah, I talked to her today too, bro.

24:13.596 --> 24:15.797
I didn't want to say anything
in case it didn't pan out.

24:15.831 --> 24:19.167
- You guys are too good to me.
- Not always.

24:19.201 --> 24:21.770
Okay, what's the bad news?

24:21.804 --> 24:25.606
- What, no luck getting money for Don Peppe's?
- No. Struck out.

24:25.641 --> 24:27.716
- Let me put in a little.
- Vince, no.

24:27.882 --> 24:29.644
You know, I feel like
he's trying to cut me out.

24:29.678 --> 24:32.079
The guy's got his hands on a potential
gold mine and I can't get a piece.

24:32.114 --> 24:34.448
Yeah. What, are we gonna have
to pay for our own baked clams?

24:34.482 --> 24:36.751
Very selfish.

24:36.785 --> 24:38.519
Okay, what's wrong?

24:38.685 --> 24:41.722
I really was trying to do
this myself, you know?

24:41.756 --> 24:45.259
- You've done so much for me, Vin.
- What happened?

24:45.293 --> 24:49.497
- Avion went public today.
- It did?

24:49.532 --> 24:51.432
And if not for my selfish desire

24:51.467 --> 24:53.534
to prove that I don't need you,

24:53.568 --> 24:55.036
if we didn't sell our stock,

24:55.070 --> 24:57.171
I would've made almost $4 million.

24:57.205 --> 25:01.309
And what's worse...
You would've made almost 15.

25:01.343 --> 25:03.510
- Jesus.
- Wow, that's unbelievable.

25:03.545 --> 25:07.381
I'm sorry, Vin.
I'm so stupid.

25:07.415 --> 25:10.784
You're not stupid. You're smart for
getting me into this tequila thing.

25:10.819 --> 25:13.187
And I'm smart for not
fucking listening to you.

25:13.221 --> 25:15.389
- What?
- I never sold.

25:15.555 --> 25:18.259
- Wait, what do you mean?
- I knew this thing was going to be huge

25:18.293 --> 25:20.027
because you told me
it was going to be

25:20.061 --> 25:22.463
and because I called mark
Cuban who guaranteed it.

25:22.497 --> 25:25.032
So I kept my shares
and I even bought yours.

25:25.067 --> 25:27.268
Don't fuck with me right now, Vin.
Please?

25:27.302 --> 25:29.537
Cuban told me I'd regret
it forever if I didn't,

25:29.571 --> 25:31.406
so I bought them for you.

25:31.440 --> 25:33.308
I mean, you gotta
give me back the initial,

25:33.342 --> 25:35.143
but seems like a good trade...

25:35.177 --> 25:36.910
$300,000 for almost $4 million.

25:37.076 --> 25:40.414
- Turtle's a millionaire?
- Yeah. And nowhat he doesn't need me,

25:40.448 --> 25:42.617
maybe he'll let me invest
in his restaurant.

25:44.586 --> 25:46.621
I... I don't know what to say.

25:46.655 --> 25:48.823
Say "thank you," you dumb fuck.

25:48.857 --> 25:51.425
Thank you, Vin.

25:52.994 --> 25:55.963
Thank <i>you</i> for the
good words for Sophia.

25:55.997 --> 25:59.032
I have a feeling a lot of good
stuff is coming to all of us.

25:59.066 --> 26:01.634
- Agreed.
- Do me a favor...

26:01.668 --> 26:04.170
Call E, tell him I can't make dinner.

26:04.204 --> 26:06.406
You got it, boss.

26:06.440 --> 26:08.541
I love that guy.

26:15.917 --> 26:17.918
Jesus Christ.

26:17.953 --> 26:19.487
What the fuck are you doing, Eric?

26:19.521 --> 26:22.056
- I wanted to talk to you.
- I don't want to talk to you.

26:22.090 --> 26:23.657
- I wanted to apologize.
- Save it.

26:23.692 --> 26:25.083
- And I didn't mean it.
- <i>Oh, you didn't?</i>

26:25.249 --> 26:28.429
- I know it was mean.
- You are mean, Eric,

26:28.464 --> 26:30.465
only I didn't realize it
until recently.

26:30.499 --> 26:32.799
- I'm not mean, Sloan. I just--
- You just?

26:32.965 --> 26:35.385
- I want to get back together.
- That will never happen.

26:35.551 --> 26:38.472
- Why? Because of Johnny Galecki?
- Please just leave me alone.

26:38.638 --> 26:40.557
Sloan, I was hurt, okay?

26:40.723 --> 26:42.943
And I couldn't stand seeing
you with some asshole.

26:42.978 --> 26:44.612
I was never with him.

26:44.646 --> 26:47.348
We went out once and I
had lunch with him today

26:47.382 --> 26:49.317
to tell him it couldn't work.

26:49.351 --> 26:50.984
- Why couldn't it work?
- It doesn't matter.

26:51.150 --> 26:53.195
- Because you're not over me.
- It doesn't matter.

26:53.361 --> 26:55.892
Why can't you just admit that
you still have feelings for me?

26:55.926 --> 27:00.264
My family hates you, Eric.
And I love them.

27:00.298 --> 27:04.101
So even if I wasn't over you,
I could never be with you,

27:04.136 --> 27:06.203
so it doesn't matter.

27:06.237 --> 27:08.839
So please just leave me alone.

27:10.442 --> 27:12.810
Look, I just want you to know that

27:12.844 --> 27:15.312
I'm sorry for everything
I've ever done to you.

27:15.347 --> 27:17.748
You've done more than you know.

27:17.783 --> 27:19.917
What do you mean?

27:21.220 --> 27:23.288
What does that mean, Sloan?

27:23.322 --> 27:25.790
I'm pregnant, E.

27:25.824 --> 27:28.093
And as much as you think I'm a slut,

27:28.127 --> 27:31.858
I haven't been with anyone
<i>but</i> you, so it's yours.

27:32.024 --> 27:36.969
- Wow, Sloan, I mean...
- I'm going to New York like I planned.

27:37.003 --> 27:41.473
And I don't want or need
anything from you, <i>ever.</i>

